x4freetext: Faraday cup
Two self-supporting Al targets 40 mu-g and 80 mu-g
thick; the targets and  the particle detectors were
mounted in the scattering chamber under vacuum; the
detector rotated around the target.
A telescope device. It consists
of two silicon detectors  stacked and connected in
parallel to the same amplifier system. Two totally
depleted OBTEC G J 025 surface barrier detectors
transmission mounted, 80 mu-m and 500 mu-m thick,
respectively.
A fixed silicon counter, detecting elastically
scattered deuterons at 90.  degr. was used as a monitor
The overall incident energy resolution was of
the order of 10 keV and 20  keV,  respectively.
